post_text:
This morning our district was the subject of a significant data surge within our internet system. Our protective firewall immediately shut down our internet as a safety response and precautionary measure. Once our technicians confirmed that all systems and data were secure, service was restored. Our system was down for approximately two hours because of this incident.

We truly appreciate your patience and cooperation during this untimely shutdown and hope instruction is now continuing across the district.

Los Fresnos CISD is excited to share that we are rolling out ReminddDistrict-wide! If you're not already familiar with Remind, it's a classroom communication tool that makes it easy to stay involved with your child's learning. Remind is free to use, and you'll be able to get and send messages on any device ‚Äì even a simple text message from your phone!

As part of this rollout, official accounts will be created for all the educators, parents, and students at Los Fresnos CISD. If you had a phone number on file with us you may have already received a text message from Remind promoting you to set up an account or join a class.

For more information including a link to a video demo about how Remind works, visit this link: https://www.lfcisd.net/apps/news/article/1288647

post_text:
Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time benefit of up to $285 and will be issued on an EBT card to assist families during this unanticipated school closure. The P-EBT application is now open.

Your household may be eligible to receive P-EBT benefits to buy food from any retailer that accepts the Texas Lone Star Card.

P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

post_text: It's Homecoming Parade time! All Los Fresnos CISD schools will be participating in the annual Homecoming Parade at 5:30 p.m. Thursday. On Friday night, there is a Tailgating event at the Los Fresnos Elementary playground across the parking lot from the stadium. The Falcons take on Edinburg Vela at 7:30 p.m. Friday. On Saturday, students will participate in the Homecoming Dance.

People
March 26, 2014 at 3:56 PM ¬∑

http://peoplem.ag/v0OCj

Inspired by their blind classmate, these Texas middle schoolers invented an app to help those with visual impairments navigate new spaces.

Called Hello Navi, the app is designed to measure a user's stride and combine this information with digital building blueprints, to then give verbal directions that can help users easily navigate unfamiliar spaces.

Click here to read more about these inventive students: http://peoplem.ag/v0OCj

Road closure 8 a.m. update: The two bridges over railroad tracks at the FM 1847/FM 511 area remain closed, and could reopen as early as 10 a.m., Brownsville police reported. One bridge is on FM 1847 just south of FM 511, and the other is FM 511 between Alton Gloor Boulevard and FM 1847.

If you are trying to get to Los Fresnos schools from Brownsville, you must use the Interstate 69E frontage roads to FM 511 to reach Rancho Verde Elementary, or I69E frontage road to FM 803 to reach Texas Highway 100 and other district schools.

After discussion with the Cameron County Division of Emergency Management and the National Weather Service this morning about updated weather information, Los Fresnos CISD will continue with normal operations for Wednesday and Thursday. Elementary schools begin at 7:50 a.m., middle schools begin at 8:20 a.m., and high schools begin at 8:25 a.m.

Our schools will be warmer than homes for many of our students.

We will continue to monitor weather conditions and will make further announcements if necessary. Thank you.

The much-anticipated FM 803 realignment project will improve traffic along a new highway from Rancho Viejo to Texas Highway 100 at 9 a.m. Friday.

The opening of the two-mile stretch of the FM 803 at its southern point at I-69E provides Los Fresnos United, a campus with almost 1,800 students, a smoother traffic flow. The road will be four lanes with a continuous left-turn lane in front of the school.

For more information, visit goo.gl/6caebh.

post_text:
Attention Falcon Football Fans!

Los Fresnos CISD would like to gauge the interest of adult Falcon Football fans interested in riding on a charter bus for the Los Fresnos-San Antonio Southwest Area playoff game at 1 p.m. Saturday at Alamo Stadium in San Antonio.

We need to find out how many adult fans are willing to ride the charter bus to and from San Antonio for the game Saturday. The cost would be between $35 and $45 per person, depending on the number of fans riding. The bus has a capacity of 55 passengers.

Game ticket is not included.

We must have a minimum of 42 passengers for this charter bus idea to work and need commitments by noon Thursday. A contract would need to be made with the bus company Thursday. If fewer than 42 adults show an interest, this idea would be scrapped.

If you would like to be part of this charter bus trip for the game, call 956-254-5098 during business hours to add your name of people making a commitment to pay the $35-$45 for the charter bus trip, or send an email to rzamora@lfcisd.net.

Thank you.
text:
Attention Falcon Football Fans!

Los Fresnos CISD would like to gauge the interest of adult Falcon Football fans interested in riding on a charter bus for the Los Fresnos-San Antonio Southwest Area playoff game at 1 p.m. Saturday at Alamo Stadium in San Antonio.

We need to find out how many adult fans are willing to ride the charter bus to and from San Antonio for the game Saturday. The cost would be between $35 and $45 per person, depending on the number of fans riding. The bus has a capacity of 55 passengers.

Game ticket is not included.

We must have a minimum of 42 passengers for this charter bus idea to work and need commitments by noon Thursday. A contract would need to be made with the bus company Thursday. If fewer than 42 adults show an interest, this idea would be scrapped.

If you would like to be part of this charter bus trip for the game, call 956-254-5098 during business hours to add your name of people making a commitment to pay the $35-$45 for the charter bus trip, or send an email to rzamora@lfcisd.net.

Thank you.
